de up of all possible results (in our example, the event {1,2,3,4,5,6}) is =
assigned a value of one. To qualify as a probability, the assignment of val=
ues must satisfy the requirement that for any collection of mutually exclus=
ive events (events with no common results, such as the events {1,6}, {3}, a=
nd {2,4}), the probability that at least one of the events will occur is gi=
ven by the sum of the probabilities of all the individual events.<sup id=3D=
"cite_ref-30" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
